16´À 13:27 "Do we then hear about you that you have committed all this great evil by acting unfaithfully against our God by marrying foreign women?"
16´À 13:28 Even one of the sons of Joiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest, was a son-in-law of Sanballat the Horonite, so I drove him away from me.
16´À 13:29 Remember them, O my God, because they have defiled the priesthood and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites.
16´À 13:30 Thus I purified them from everything foreign and appointed duties for the priests and the Levites, each in his task,
16´À 13:31 and [I arranged] for the supply of wood at appointed times and for the first fruits. Remember me, O my God, for good.
